      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im working on this script to process some huge csv files with pandas but im getting a MemoryError every time i run it. i think it might be because of how i'm loading the data. can u explain the main difference between using a list comprehension vs a generator function when im trying to loop through these rows? like which one is better for keeping memory usage low?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A list comprehension builds the entire list in memory at once, which can be disastrous for huge files. In contrast, a generator function or generator expression yields items one at a time, only calculating the next value when it's specifically requested. For keeping memory usage low when processing massive CSVs, the generator approach is vastly superior because it streams the data without ever needing to hold the whole dataset in RAM. You should definitely use generators for large datasets to avoid those dreaded `MemoryError` exceptions.",
      "source": "target",
