      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if i switch to a generator i should be okay? i'm also seeing some weird behavior where the memory usage just keeps climbing higher and higher even when i'm not doing much, like it's just constantly eating up my available RAM. is that just how python works or is there something else that might be \"stealing\" my resources in the background?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A generator will certainly help manage the *input* data efficiently, but persistent memory climbing suggests a different issue, likely related to object retention or caching within your code. Python's garbage collector is usually good, but if you are accidentally storing intermediate results or creating references to large objects within loops, those objects won't be released. It's worth checking if any variables outside the loop are accumulating references to the data being processed.",
