      "content": "If you suspect a memory leak, you need proper profiling tools to track down the culprit rather than relying on guesswork. Tools like `memory_profiler` or Python's built-in `tracemalloc` can give you line-by-line visibility into where memory is being allocated and held onto. Running your script under one of these profilers will tell you precisely which function or line of code is retaining those unexpected resources. This is the most reliable way to pinpoint what your script is unknowingly holding onto.",
